honeywell.printer

Class ParametersDPL

  • java.lang.Object
    • honeywell.printer.Parameters
      • honeywell.printer.ParametersDPL

  • public class ParametersDPL
extends Parameters
    This class represents the general parameters that can be used to alter the printing characteristics when 'printing' to a DocumentDPL object. Printing characteristics are 'local' to each print command they are passed into. To have global settings the same parameters object can be passed into each write call to the Document object.

      • getAlignment

        public ParametersDPL.Alignment getAlignment()
        This is the horizontal alignment to use when writing the item. The options are:
        • Alignment.Left - Left aligned. This will write the item starting at the column specified in the write command.
        • Alignment.Center - Center aligned. This will write the item centered at the column specified in the write command.
        • Alignment.Right - Right aligned. This will write the item flush against the right side of the column specified in the write command.
        Returns:
        Alignment setting to use.

      • setHorizontalMultiplier

        public void setHorizontalMultiplier(int value)
        The horizontal multiplier property will cause the horizontal printing of the object to be scaled by that amount. So a value of two would cause a printing of the object to be double its original width. The default value for this parameter is 1 and the range of valid values is 1 to 61.
        Parameters:
        value - Factor by which to scale the printing horizontally.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the parameter values are not in the valid range.
        Since:
        1.0.0

      • setVerticalMultiplier

        public void setVerticalMultiplier(int value)
        The vertical multiplier property will cause the vertical printing of the object to be scaled by that amount. So a value of two would cause a printing of the object to be double its original hieght. The default value for this parameter is 1 and the range of valid values is 1 to 255.
        Parameters:
        value - Factor by which to scale the printing vertically.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the parameter values are not in the valid range.
        Since:
        1.0.0

      • setRotate

        public void setRotate(ParametersDPL.Rotation rotationAngle)
               throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        This is the number of degrees the printing will be rotated about the starting location in the counter-clockwise direction. The default value for this parameter is 0 degrees.
        Parameters:
        rotationAngle - Number of degrees to rotate the printing the range of valid values is 0, 90, 180 or 270 degrees.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the parameter values are not in the valid range.
        Since:
        2.1.0
